headline.main: Play by Lawrence and Lee at Broadhurst

results.snippet: BECAUSE "A Call on Kuprin" is so timely that it seems to jump from this year's headlines, it would have been easy to settle for a simple-minded cloak-and-dagger thriller based on the news. But Jerome Lawrence and Robert E. Lee have elected to aim...
results.lead_paragraph: BECAUSE "A Call on Kuprin" is so timely that it seems to jump from this year's headlines, it would have been easy to settle for a simple-minded cloak-and-dagger thriller based on the news. But Jerome Lawrence and Robert E. Lee have elected to aim higher, and their new play, which arrived last night at the Broadhurst, is not only contemporary and tautly suspenseful but also says something of vast importance.
